reviews.review: I found it to be extremely entertaining, and it delivered on everything I hoped to see and then some.

Okay. Welp. The Rise of Skywalker may not win any "film" awards, but I am one damned happy Star Wars fan right now. Call it a guilty pleasure, maybe it is a bit TOO much of a movie for "the fans," but I can't remember the last time I grinned during an entire movie like this. TLJ may be a good "film" but not a great Star Wars film (to me). I need to see this more, but my god I was just EATING IT UP. I wanted more, and more and more. It was epic, emotional, heavy, tragic, exciting, etc. There are problems, of course, and it is kind of a mess of a film in some ways. They literally crammed 2 movies into one. I wore a dorky Star Wars xmas sweater to the theater, and I was afraid that I would be taking it off at home in disappointment or even disgust (some people, and film critics don't like the movie)... but man, now I want to wear the thing on my friggin' head. Very happy fan right now. Honestly, after seeing this, TLJ feels like a weird side-story that doesn't even fit into the trilogy. JJ should have had the whole thing, or they should have made this movie into Pt1 and 2 like the Deathly Hollows.
I loved it! The ending was so satisfying and the storyline was so pure :) it featured so many nostalgic things from the originals and it made me so happy! I’m definitely going to see it again!
A perfect ending to an amazing saga
The first 2 hours are amazing and really put together but then kind of starts falling apart in the end. Still great :)

JJ Abrams solidified himself as a fantastic choice for Star Wars with Force Awakens. With The Rise of Skywalker he completely knocks it out of the park. 
Spectacular, jaw dropping, pulse pounding, and tear jerking; Rise of Skywalker is everything about Star Wars I love.

Unbearable in a bad sense and fully second-hand with all possible cliche and episodes from the "must be list". This is not the ending of the story for a generation, just one more mediocre space-something-blockbuster.
